        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 3:54PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Maryneal, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sweetwater, Blackwell, Nolan, Merkel, Trent, Hylton, Maryneal, Shep,
Lake Sweetwater, Camp Butman, The Intersection Of Highway 70 And
Ranch Road 53, The Intersection Of Ranch Road 608 And Highway 147,
and Camp Boothe Oaks.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 239 and 274.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
